             Former Australian Prime Minister
Kevin Rudd is recovering well after an operation to remove his
gallbladder, the Australian Broadcasting Corp. reported.  
 Rudd, 52, was taken to the Mater Private Hospital in
Brisbane with acute abdominal pain two days ago, according to
his office. He is likely to return home in a couple of days
after the operation late yesterday, the broadscaster reported,
citing Ruddâ€™s doctors.  
          
          


  


        